This page is meant to be a place to collect information about open access journals or journal articles about climate science and policy. Feel free to add! (NOTE: This is **not** a place for links to blog posts, though you're welcome to start another page for that.  Ideally, this list will focus on peer-reviewed literature)

**LIST OF OPEN-ACCESS JOURNALS**

To start, here's a link to the "Earth & Environmental Sciences" page of the Directory of Open Access Journals. [DOAJ](http://www.doaj.org/doaj?func=subject&cpId=78&uiLanguage=en)

* [American Journal of Climate Change](http://www.scirp.org/journal/ajcc/)

* [Boletín de Ciencias de la Tierra](http://www.revistas.unal.edu.co/index.php/rbct)

* [British Journal of Environment and Climate Change](http://www.sciencedomain.org/journal-home.php?id=10)

* [Earth Science India](http://www.earthscienceindia.info/)

* [Earth Sciences Research Journal](http://www.revistas.unal.edu.co/index.php/esrj/index)

* [Geologica Acta: an International Earth Science Journal](http://www.geologica-acta.com/HomeAC.do)

* [Journal of Earth Science & Climatic Change](http://www.omicsonline.org/jescchome.php)

* [Journal of Environmental Science and Technology](http://www.scialert.net/jindex.php?issn=1994-7887)

* [Research Journal of Environmental and Earth Sciences](http://maxwellsci.com/jp/j2p.php?jid=RJEES)

* [Revista de Climatología](http://webs.ono.com/reclim/)

**LIST OF SPECIFIC OPEN-ACCESS ARTICLES THAT MAY BE OF INTEREST**

''Please list alphabetically by the last name of the first author''

* Cook, John, Dana Nuccitelli, Sarah A. Green, Mark Richardson, Bärbel Winkler, Rob Painting, Robert Way, Peter Jacobs, and Andrew Skuce, 2013. [Quantifying the consensus on anthropogenic global warming in the scientific literature](http://iopscience.iop.org/1748-9326/8/2/024024/article), Environmental Research Letters, vol 8, no 2. doi: 10.1088/1748-9326/8/2/024024
 [PDF](http://iopscience.iop.org/1748-9326/8/2/024024/pdf/1748-9326_8_2_024024.pdf)

* Foster, G., and S. Rahmstorf, 2011. [Global temperature evolution 1979–2010](http://iopscience.iop.org/1748-9326/6/4/044022/fulltext/), Environmental Research Letters, vol 6, 044022. doi: 10.1088/1748-9326/6/4/044022 [PDF](http://iopscience.iop.org/1748-9326/6/4/044022/pdf/1748-9326_6_4_044022.pdf)

* Griggs, J. A., J. E. Harries, 2007. [Comparison of Spectrally Resolved Outgoing Longwave Radiation over the Tropical Pacific between 1970 and 2003 Using IRIS, IMG, and AIRS](http://journals.ametsoc.org/doi/abs/10.1175/JCLI4204.1). Journal of Climate, 20, 3982-4001. doi: 10.1175/JCLI4204.1 [PDF](http://web.gps.caltech.edu/~mlau/Griggs-07-IRIS-IMG-AIRS.pdf)

* Hansen James E., and Makiko Sato, January 2012. [Paleoclimate Implications for Human-Made Climate Change](http://www.fractual.co.za/Documents/Paleoclimate_Implications.pdf). NASA Goddard Institute for Space Studies and Columbia University Earth Institute, New York.

* Hansen, James E., Makiko Sato, Gary Russell, and Pushker Kharecha, September 2013. [Climate sensitivity, sea level and atmospheric carbon dioxide](http://rsta.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/371/2001/20120294.full.html). Phil. Trans. R. Soc. A, vol 371, 20120294, published 16 September 2013. [PDF](http://rsta.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/371/2001/20120294.full.pdf+html)

* Hansen, James, Makiko Sato, Reto Ruedy, Ken Lo, David W. Lea, and Martin Medina-Elizade, 2006. [Global temperature change](http://www.pnas.org/content/103/39/14288.full?sid=c4935483-9197-4644-9f3f-830b1c8b6520), Proceedings of the National Academy of Sciences, vol 103, no 39, 14288-14293. doi: 10.1073/pnas.0606291103 [PDF](http://www.pnas.org/content/103/39/14288.full.pdf+html)

* Harries, John E., Helen E. Brindley, Peter J. Sagoo, and Richard J. Bantges, 2001. [Increases in greenhouse forcing inferred from the outgoing longwave radiation spectra of the Earth in 1970 and 1997](http://www.nature.com/nature/journal/v410/n6826/abs/410355a0.html), Nature 410, 355-357. doi: 10.1038/410355A0 [PDF](https://workspace.imperial.ac.uk/physics/Public/spat/John/Increase%20in%20greenhouse%20forcing%20inferred%20from%20the%20outgoing%20longwave%20radiation%20spectra%20of%20the%20Earth%20in%201970%20and%201997.pdf)

* Heide-Jørgensen, M.P., Kristin L. Laidre, Lori T. Quakenbush, and John J. Cittaet, 2012. [The Northwest Passage opens for bowhead whales](http://rsbl.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/8/2/270), Biology Letters, vol 8, no 2, 270-273. doi: 10.1098/rsbl.2011.0731 [PDF](http://rsbl.royalsocietypublishing.org/content/8/2/270.full.pdf+html)

* Hussein, Zekarias, Thomas Hertel, and Alla Golub, 2013. [Climate change mitigation policies and poverty in developing countries](http://iopscience.iop.org/1748-9326/8/3/035009), Environmental Research Letters, vol 8. doi:10.1088/1748-9326/8/3/035009 [PDF](http://iopscience.iop.org/1748-9326/8/3/035009/pdf/1748-9326_8_3_035009.pdf)

* International Energy Agency, 2013. [Redrawing the Energy-Climate Map](http://www.worldenergyoutlook.org/energyclimatemap/). [PDF](http://www.worldenergyoutlook.org/media/weowebsite/2013/energyclimatemap/RedrawingEnergyClimateMap.pdf) 

* Kharecha, Pushker A., and James E. Hansen, 2013. [Prevented Mortality and Greenhouse Gas Emissions from Historical and Projected Nuclear Power](http://pubs.acs.org/doi/full/10.1021/es3051197), Environ. Sci. Technol., vol. 47, no. 9, 4889–4895. doi: 10.1021/es3051197 [PDF](http://pubs.acs.org/doi/pdf/10.1021/es3051197)

* Kouketsu, Shinya et al, 2011. [Deep ocean heat content changes estimated from observation and reanalysis product and their influence on sea level change](http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1029/2010JC006464/abstract), Journal of Geophysical Research: Oceans, vol. 116 iss. C3. doi: 10.1029/2010JC006464 [PDF](ftp://soest.hawaii.edu/coastal/Climate%20Articles/Ocean%20warming%20DEEP%20Kouketsu%202011.pdf)

* Levitus, S., J.I. Antonov, T.P. Boyer, O.K. Baranova, H.E. Garcia, R.A. Locarnini, A.V. Mishonov, J.R. Reagan, D. Seidov, E.S. Yarosh, and M.M. Zweng, 2012. [World ocean heat content and thermosteric sea level change (0–2000 m), 1955–2010](http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1029/2012GL051106/abstract). Geophysical Research Letters, vol. 39, iss. 10, L10603. doi:10.1029/2012GL051106 [PDF](ftp://kakapo.ucsd.edu/pub/sio_220/e03%20-%20Global%20warming/Levitus_et_al.GRL12.pdf)

* Lobell, David B., and Sharon M. Gourdji, 2012. [The Influence of Climate Change on Global Crop Productivity](http://www.plantphysiol.org/content/160/4/1686.full), Plant Physiology, vol. 160 no. 4 1686-1697 doi: ​10.​1104/​pp.​112.​208298 [PDF](http://www.plantphysiol.org/content/160/4/1686.full.pdf+html)

* Murphy, D. M., S. Solomon, R. W. Portmann, K. H. Rosenlof, P. M. Forster, and T. Wong, 2009. [An observationally based energy balance for the Earth since 1950](http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1029/2009JD012105/abstract), Journal of Geophysical Research, vol. 114 iss. D17. doi: 10.1029/2009JD012105 [PDF](http://www.iup.uni-heidelberg.de/institut/studium/lehre/Uphysik/PhysicsClimate/2009JD012105.pdf)

* Shepherd, Andrew et al, 2012. [A Reconciled Estimate of Ice-Sheet Mass Balance](http://www.sciencemag.org/content/338/6111/1183), Science, vol. 338 no. 6111 1183-1189 doi: 10.1126/science.1228102 [PDF](http://www.staff.science.uu.nl/~lenae101/pubs/Shepherd2012.pdf)

* Thackeray, Stephen J. et al, 2010. [Trophic level asynchrony in rates of phenological change for marine, freshwater and terrestrial environments](http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1365-2486.2010.02165.x/full), Global Change Biology, vol. 16 iss. 12 3304-3313 doi: 10.1111/j.1365-2486.2010.02165.x [PDF](http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1365-2486.2010.02165.x/pdf)
